jot.ai.pathFinders

Class AbstractPathFinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • jot.ai.pathFinders.AbstractPathFinder
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AStar, BestFirstSearch, Dijkstra, FringeSearch

    public abstract class AbstractPathFinder
extends Object
    Abstract class that each pathfinder must implement. Alternatively one massive class may be implemented instead.
    Author:
    G. Amador & A. Gomes

      • findPath

        public abstract org.apache.commons.math3.geometry.euclidean.threed.Vector3D[] findPath(org.apache.commons.math3.geometry.euclidean.threed.Vector3D startPosition,
                                                                                       org.apache.commons.math3.geometry.euclidean.threed.Vector3D goalPosition,
                                                                                       long timeout)
        This methods returns a path if found using either a default or a provided pathFinder logic.
        Parameters:
        startPosition - the Cartesian coordinates of the starting node.
        goalPosition - the Cartesian coordinates of the destination node.
        timeout - the amount of time at most a pathfinder can attempt to find a path.
        Returns:
        if a path is found returns, an array of Vector3D coordinates of the points to go from an start to an target position. Otherwise returns NULL.
